message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the generation of words from a context-free language.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for non-redundant generation of words.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses the limits of a rejection-based approach, which involves combinatorial analysis.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper analyzes the time complexity of the rejection-based approach and proposes an alternative algorithm with better complexity.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the implementation of the algorithm and the precomputation of numbers, which could involve geometric concepts.
